  "texts": [
    "Graph is an F1 metrics of the matched edges after the node alignment by bipartite matching.",
    "This metric is for the similarity measurement of the entire graph structure, ignoring the textual differences of nodes and edges after the alignment.",
    "Let the node set V r and edge set E r composes reference graph G r, and the node set V h and edge set E h composes hypothesis (generated) graph G h.",
    "Using a node alignment function a(•): V h → {V r, ϕ} from the generated graph nodes V h to the reference graph nodes V r and Kronecker delta δ µν = 1 iif µ = ν otherwise δ µν = 0, which represents the agreement of the nodes here, we compute the agreement score of the nodes as f Graph (e h, e r) = δ a(v s,h)vs,r δ a(v e,h)ve,r.",
    "v s,h and v s,r are the start nodes of each edge from the hypothesis (generated) and reference graphs, while v e,h and v e,r are the end nodes of it, respectively."
